  (RCE) vulnerability in the mariadb-dump Utility.|insight=The specific flaw exists within the handling of view names. The
  issue results from the lack of proper validation of a user-supplied path prior to using it in file
  operations. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to execute code in the context of the
  current user.|affected=MariaDB versions prior to 10.6.24, 10.7.x prior to 10.11.15,
  11.x prior to 11.4.9 and 11.5.x prior to 11.8.4.|impact=This vulnerability allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary
  code on affected installations of MariaDB. Interaction with the mariadb-dump utility is required
  to exploit this vulnerability but attack vectors may vary depending on the implementation.|solution=Update to version 10.6.24, 10.11.15, 11.4.9, 11.8.4 or
  later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
